===Etymology===
From Early Modern English {{term|pleasur|lang=en}}, {{term|plesur|lang=en}}, alteration (with ending accommodated to {{term|-ure|lang=en}}), of {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|plaisir||pleasure|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|plesir|lang=fro}}, {{term|plaisir||to please|lang=fro}}, infinitive used as a noun, conjugated form of {{term|plaisir|lang=fro}} or {{term|plaire|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|placeo|placēre|lang=la|to please, to seem good}}, from the {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*plā-k-||wide and flat}}. More at {{l|en|please}}.

