===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} A [[state]] of being [[please]]d.
#: {{usex|lang=en|He remembered with '''pleasure''' his home and family.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|I get a lot of '''pleasure''' from watching others work hard while I relax.}}
#* {{quote-news|year=2012|date=April 22|author=Sam Sheringham|work=BBC Sport
|title=[http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17718147 Liverpool 0-1 West Brom]
|passage=But the only statistic that will concern West Brom will be the scoreline, and their manager Roy Hodgson will take considerable '''pleasure''' from a victory over the club he managed for just 191 days.}}
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A [[person]], [[thing]] or [[action]] that [[cause]]s [[enjoyment]].
#: {{usex|lang=en|It was a '''pleasure''' to meet you.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|Having a good night's sleep is one of life's little '''pleasures'''.}}
#* Bible, {{w|Acts of the Apostles|Acts}} xxv. 9
#*: Festus, willing to do the Jews a '''pleasure'''
#* {{quote-book|year=1898|author={{w|Winston Churchill (novelist)|Winston Churchill}}
|title={{w|The Celebrity}}|chapter=8
|passage=The humor of my proposition appealed more strongly to Miss Trevor than I had looked for, and from that time forward she became her old self again;{{...}}. Now she had come to look upon the matter in its true proportions, and her anticipation of a possible chance of teaching him a lesson was a '''pleasure''' to behold.}}
#* {{quote-magazine|date=2013-05-17|author=George Monbiot|authorlink=George Monbiot
|volume=188|issue=23|page=19|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}
|title=[http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2013/may/06/politics-envy-keenest-rich Money just makes the rich suffer]
|passage=In order to grant the rich these '''pleasures''', the social contract is reconfigured. The welfare state is dismantled.&nbsp;[&hellip;]}}
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} One's [[preference]].
#: {{usex|lang=en|What is your '''pleasure''': coffee or tea?}}
# {{context|formal|uncountable|lang=en}} The [[will]] or [[desire]] of someone or some agency in [[power]].
#: {{usex|lang=en|to hold an office at '''pleasure''': to hold it indefinitely until it is revoked}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|to be imprisoned [[at Her Majesty's pleasure|at Her Majesty's '''pleasure''']]'': to be imprisoned indefinitely}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|at Congress's '''pleasure''': whenever or as long as Congress desires}}
#* Bible, {{w|Book of Isaiah|Isaiah}} xlviii. 14
#*: He will do his '''pleasure''' on Babylon.
#* {{w|William Shakespeare}} (1564-1616)
#*: Use your '''pleasure'''; if your love do not persuade you to come, let not my letter.

